loadClass

  • loadClass(class_name: any, module_name: any, registry: any, require_error: any): Promise<any>
    • Defined in utils.ts:59

    Tries to load a class

    Tries to load a class from a module using require.js, if a module is specified, otherwise tries to load a class from the global registry, if the global registry is provided.

    The optional require_error argument is a function that takes the success handler and returns a requirejs error handler, which may call the success handler with a fallback module.

    Parameters

    • class_name: any
    • module_name: any
    • registry: any
    • require_error: any

    Returns Promise<any>
